      "span_text": "According to previous studies [CITATION_1] ) and the current data, the electrophysiological analysis of the N2 component was focused on a time window of 300-550 ms (average for the electrodes at F3, Fz, F4, FC3, FCz, and FC4), while the P3 component was 500 ms to 700 ms (average for the electrodes at CP3, CPZ, CP4, P3, PZ, and P4)."
